iFirst, lets talk about the naming of things.		gopher.black	70
i		gopher.black	70
i"Gemini" is the protocol. It appears to be capitalized in all		gopher.black	70
ioccurences within solderpunk's FAQ. 		gopher.black	70
i		gopher.black	70
i"Gemini maps" are the temporary term for the document format of		gopher.black	70
ia Gemini server. It's coined by solderpunk here [1] and only named		gopher.black	70
ithat "until a better name comes along."		gopher.black	70
i		gopher.black	70
0[1] Gemini maps	/~solderpunk/gemini/gemini-maps.txt	zaibatsu.circumlunar.space	70
i		gopher.black	70
i"Geminiholes" - mentioned by solderpunk, but noone is using it.		gopher.black	70
i		gopher.black	70
i"Gemini server/client" are the defacto name for individual tools		gopher.black	70
ithat power it.		gopher.black	70
i		gopher.black	70
i"Gemini-verse / Gemini-sphere / Gemini ecosystem" - I haven't		gopher.black	70
inoted any special term for this akin to "the web" or		gopher.black	70
i"gopherspace". Is there something already in use?		gopher.black	70
i		gopher.black	70
i"Journal" - weB LOG / goPHer LOG like structure. Is there		gopher.black	70
ia playful term for these yet?		gopher.black	70
i		gopher.black	70
iWhat other terms are we missing?		gopher.black	70
