iOkay, enough of that. Time for THOUGHTS OF IMPORTANCE!		gopher.black	70
i		gopher.black	70
iThe built-in TLS by design of Gemini is great, and combined with		gopher.black	70
ithe natural ability to run it unpriviliged and require very little		gopher.black	70
ibandwidth I can see it serving a valuable purpose in safely		gopher.black	70
iproviding a platform for authors in situations where the web is		gopher.black	70
inot. Take Khazikstan, for instance, who is MITMing the entire		gopher.black	70
icountry. Gopher was always a nice idea to help in these		gopher.black	70
isituations, but the lack of reliable security on it meant major		gopher.black	70
iproblems for real applications. Gemini fixes that. What's more,		gopher.black	70
iGemini over tor adds in anonymity.		gopher.black	70
i		gopher.black	70
iI have more thoughts on the tor thing, and around real-world		gopher.black	70
iapplications for a minimalist hyperlinkable publishing protocol		gopher.black	70
iwith built in anonymity and safety, but my internet connection is		gopher.black	70
idying and I have to finish this post while tethered to my phone.		gopher.black	70
iThank goodness for low bandwidth stuff like gopher and Gemini,		gopher.black	70
iright?		gopher.black	70
